> Creamy colcannon is a traditional Irish dish of mashed potato and kale and was originally served in a dish with a dip in the centre that was filled with melted butter. In this dish, we've used cavolo nero (a variety of kale) and stirred through wholegrain mustard for an added kick of flavour.

Fill and boil your #kettle{} and preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Pop the @Tuscan Pork Sausages{4} on a #baking tray{} and roast them on the top shelf of your oven until browned and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}, turning halfway through cooking. IMPORTANT: The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, chop the @Potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). Pop them in a large #saucepan{} along with @salt{0.5%tsp}, cover with boiling water and put onto high heat. Boil the potatoes until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Red Onion{1}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a small #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the onion and cook until softened and beginning to brown, ~{5-7%minutes}. Stir often. This is the base of your gravy.

When the potatoes have 5 minutes left, add the @Chopped Cavolo Nero{100%g} to the saucepan of potatoes. Submerge the cavolo nero in the boiling water or cover with a #lid{} so it cooks. Cook until tender, ~{5%minutes}.

Lower the heat of the pan with the onions to medium and add the @Balsamic Vinegar{12%ml}. Cook until almost evaporated. Add the @Water{100%ml} to the pan and bring to the boil. Stir in the @KNORR Chicken Stock{1/2} and @Redcurrant Jelly{25%g} to dissolve. Simmer for ~{2-3%minutes} until the sauce has thickened slightly.

Meanwhile, drain the potatoes and cavolo nero in a #colander{} then return to the saucepan. Mash together with a #potato masher{} and then mix in the @Wholegrain Mustard{1%tsp} and a knob of @?butter{} (if you have some). Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} - colcannon made! Share the colcannon between your plates and serve the sausages alongside. Spoon the gravy over the sausages and tuck in!